    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano </strong>and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper </strong>and<strong> sugar</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>pizza sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Roughly chop your<strong> basil</strong>, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>pizza sauce</strong> between your <strong>tortillas </strong>(make sure to only cover one half of the tortilla with the sauce!)</p><p>Top the sauce evenly with the <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, <strong>chopped basil</strong>, <strong>pepperoni slices </strong>and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Fold each tortilla over so you're left with 3<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>half moon-shaped sandwiches per person\u2013 these are your <strong>loaded quesadillas</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>loaded quesadillas </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Place a second baking tray on top to weigh them down slightly</p><p>Put the stacked baking trays in the oven and cook for 12 min, or until the quesadillas are slightly browned and the cheese has melted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and shred</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Combine your<strong> mayo </strong>with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the quesadillas are slightly browned, remove the stacked trays from the oven and leave them to cool for 1 min</p><p>Tip: This makes it easier to transfer the quesadillas to a board without losing any filling!</p><p>Chop the <strong>quesadillas</strong> in half \u2013 these are your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>pepperoni pizza quesadillas</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-pepperoni-pizza-quesadillas-with-crunchy-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>pepperoni pizza quesadillas</strong> with the<strong> shredded lettuce</strong> and <strong>chopped tomato</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the<strong> creamy dressing</strong> all over the salad</p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
